# AI Screenshot Reading Implementation Plan

This plan outlines the steps to enable the "Jarvis" AI to read and understand the phone's screen by capturing screenshots and processing them using a vision-capable AI model.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Vision Model Selection**: To "read" screenshots, we need a vision-capable model. I recommend `qwen2-vl:2b` as it is highly efficient and optimized for document/screen understanding.
> **Disk Space**: Pulling `qwen2-vl:2b` will require approximately 1.5GB to 2GB of disk space in your Ollama container.
> **Hardware Requirements**: Running vision models locally requires more RAM/GPU memory than the text-only `qwen2.5:0.5b` model.

## Proposed Changes

### 1. Backend (Ollama)
We need to pull a vision-capable model to handle image inputs.

#### Instructions
Run the following command in your terminal:
```bash
docker exec -it ollama ollama pull qwen2-vl:2b
```

